    "description": "Survive the Troll is a multiplayer game in which <strong>one Troll</strong> fights against up to <strong>9 Elves</strong>.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Gameplay</h2></h2>In the Cloudy Arena, you will be provided with two kinds of gameplay:<br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2134940/extras/966d943b7d258706762defaff3bc978a.avif?t=1730051489\" width=607 height=543 /></span><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>The Troll is playing <strong>solo </strong>against all the elves. His goal? To crush every Elf he sees. To do so, he can <strong>upgrade </strong>his stats in his base, <strong>the Troll Hut</strong>. He gets passive income using troll wards, which allow him to teleport throughout the map. The Troll is hungry... Hungry for Elf meat!<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2134940/extras/bece0175d7d30f79e9d06ea1298dba4c.avif?t=1730051489\" width=474 height=380 /></span><br></li><li>The Elf is playing with a bunch of other Elves, up to a <strong>maximum of 9</strong>. In order to survive the Troll, they will have to <strong>build </strong>a base with a <strong>House</strong>, a <strong>Wall </strong>and a <strong>Tower</strong>, which attacks the Troll when it's close. Yet their goal is not to stay in their base forever, in order to continue expanding their income, they will have to cooperate in order to get <strong>gifts </strong>that contain <strong>essential</strong> resources, or troll wards! In the end, they may even take down the Troll ... ]</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Customization</h2></h2>You can customize your look with a system of <strong>skins</strong>, that you can setup and buy in the <strong>Market </strong>on the main menu.<br>You can only gain <strong>Wcoins </strong>(which are used to buy skins) by <strong>playing </strong>the game ! <br><br>This game is thought to be a &quot;chill&quot; game, so there are no ranks and ranking system.",
